    <fr:title text="Review: The Mezzanine">Review: <fr:link href="/bakerMezzanine1990/" title="The Mezzanine" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/bakerMezzanine1990/" display-uri="bakerMezzanine1990" type="local">The Mezzanine</fr:link></fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>This was a very different read for me. A short book (only 135 pages) that goes into great detail the work day at the Mezzanine. I have some gripes with the description of <html:em>readable</html:em> on the cover. I found the incredibly vivid imagery sometimes hard to follow. It seems the intent of the book was to highlight the thoughts of an ordinary working man throughout the day. However, some of these thoughs were so far from ordinary it lost the relatable, funny read it was going for. Some chapters were pure gold (the urinal) but others were a huge miss for me.</html:p>
    <html:p>Overall, I enjoyed the book and would recommend. 6.5/10.</html:p>
    <html:figure><html:img width="30%" src="/bafkrmib3htjmf6hdfuplcw7m43mtjg34v4oq4pku4jupo4lwgkt2f4njym.jpg" />
<html:figcaption>One of many book covers. Not the best IMO.</html:figcaption></html:figure>
  </fr:mainmatter>
