                <fr:title text="Review: The Infinity Machine">Review: <fr:link href="/mallabyInfinityMachineDemis2026/" title="The Infinity Machine: Demis Hassabis, DeepMind, and the Quest for Superintelligence" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/mallabyInfinityMachineDemis2026/" display-uri="mallabyInfinityMachineDemis2026" type="local">The Infinity Machine</fr:link></fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Overall, I thoroughly enjoyed this book. As a reinforcement learning afficianado, I have a newfound fandom for the mission of Deepmind. In particular, I was at the <fr:link href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pkpJMNjvgXw" type="external">RLC talk</fr:link> given by David Silver mentioned in the book. However, I must acknowledge the deep bias in favor of Demis and Deepmind in the LLM race towards the end. It is easy to come away from this, thinking that Sam Altman is some sort of Silicon Valley super villain and Demis is our champion of humanity.</html:p>
                <html:p>If I had to give an unbiased rating, I would give this book a 6.5/10. However, as a biased reader, I give it an 8/10 
  <![CDATA[:)]]></html:p>
                <html:figure><html:img width="30%" src="/bafkrmidqy4gmxy36tqca5y7bd2mmgr36d4fukrasen4gbzqf5ma7gu24de.png" />
<html:figcaption>I like this cover.</html:figcaption></html:figure>
